## **5. WEAPONS & EQUIPMENT**

### **Weapon Classes (Examples)**

Weapons are defined by **Damage Die + Action Cost**

|Weapon Type|Damage Die|Action Cost|Availability|
|---|---|---|---|
|Pistol|D4|1 action|Common/cheap|
|Assault Rifle|D6|1 action|Rare/expensive|
|Shotgun|D8|2 actions|Moderate|

**Strategic Implications:**

- Pistols: Low damage, high flexibility (can shoot multiple times)
- Assault Rifles: Balanced damage, same flexibility as pistol but harder to obtain
- Shotguns: High damage, commits you (less actions left for other things)

**Tactical Example:**

- Shoot shotgun (2 actions) + pistol (1 action) = burst damage combo

### **Weapon Skills**

Each weapon class requires skill investment:

- **Example:** Pistols (Dexterity): 3, 7, 10
- **Example:** Shotguns (Strength): 2, 6, 8

Success rate determined by skill total.

### **Ranged Combat**

**To hit a target:**

1. Check if target is within weapon range (measured in spaces/squares)
2. Roll attack (D20 ≤ weapon skill total)
3. On success, roll weapon damage die

**Range varies by weapon type** (DM/setting determines specific ranges)

### **Throwing Items**

**Throwing Distance:** Determined by Strength stat **Accuracy:** Still requires attack roll **Weight:** Heavier objects have reduced max throw distance

**Examples:**

- Grenades, rocks, improvised weapons
- Weak characters risk hurting themselves if throwing explosives too close

### **Explosives & Area of Effect**

**Blast Radius Mechanics:**

- Explosion affects circular area (e.g., 5 spaces radius)
- Damage drops off with distance from epicenter
- Different explosive types = different damage profiles

**Explosive Types:**

- **Frag Grenade:** High shrapnel damage, medium radius, sharp drop-off
- **Concussive Blast:** Lower damage, larger radius, knockback effects
- **Incendiary:** Damage over time, lingers in area, creates hazard zones

### **Equipment Tables**

Gear organized by **tier system:**

|Tier|Price Range|Availability|Example|
|---|---|---|---|
|Common|10-50 credits|Everywhere|Basic pistol, leather armor|
|Uncommon|100-300 credits|Major settlements|Quality rifle, reinforced vest|
|Rare|500-1000 credits|Specialty vendors|Plasma weapon, combat exosuit|
|Legendary|2000+ credits|Quest rewards, black market|Experimental tech, artifacts|

---

### **Equipment Weapon Slots & Load-Out Rules**

Characters may only have **two weapons actively equipped** at any time:

- **Slot 1 — One-Handed Weapon:** pistol, sword, club, dagger, wand, focus item
- **Slot 2 — Two-Handed Weapon:** assault rifle, shotgun, greatsword, polearm, staff, tome

**Swapping between your two equipped weapons is always free** — no action slot cost.

**Example Load-Outs:**

- Pistol + Assault Rifle
- Pistol + Greatsword
- Club + Shotgun
- Dagger + Polearm

**For Spellcasters:**

- Slot 1 = Focus item / Wand / Dagger
- Slot 2 = Tome / Staff
- Example Load-Outs: Wand + Tome, Dagger + Staff, Pistol + Tome

---

### **Stored Weapons & Bag Rules**

All weapons not in your two Equipment Slots are considered **stored** and must be kept in a bag.

> _(If you don't have a bag, purchase one.)_

**Accessing stored weapons:**

- **In combat:** Digging through your bag to swap a stored weapon into an Equipment Slot costs **1 ACT slot**
- **Out of combat:** Swapping stored weapons costs nothing

> **Note:** Only weapons in your two Equipment Slots are considered accessible. All others are stored and require 1 ACT to retrieve and equip — even if a weapon is physically carried on your back, it **cannot be accessed** unless it is equipped in an Equipment Slot.

> **Note:** Throwables (grenades, throwing knives, etc.) count as a **one-handed weapon** and occupy Slot 1.

