## **7. HEALING & MEDICINE**

### **Healing Types**

**PATCHING UP (Field Medicine)**

- **Skill Requirement:** Lower (easier success roll)
- **HP Restored:** Moderate amount
- **Time:** Quick (can be done mid-encounter as action)
- **Risk:** Crit fail (Natural 20) = **DAMAGES patient instead of healing**

**SURGERY (Advanced Medicine)**

- **Skill Requirement:** Higher (harder success roll, stat-dependent)
- **HP Restored:** Large amount OR fixes critical injuries
- **Time:** Longer (must be done during short rest or out of combat)
- **Risk:**
    - Any failure = **damages patient**
    - Bad failure = **PERMANENT damage** (requires proper surgery to fix)

### **Medical Skill Examples**

- Medicine (Intelligence): 4, 7, 11
- Roll D20 ≤ 11 for successful healing
- Natural 1: Perfect healing (bonus HP or removes complication)
- Natural 20: Critical failure (patient takes damage)

