## **10. DOWNTIME & RESTS**

### **Short Rest**

**Requirements:**

- 1 ration consumed per person
- Time to rest (usually 1-2 hours)
- **Risk:** Chance of enemy encounter during rest

**Benefits:**

- Restore 1 magic die size
- Perform Surgery
- Craft items
- Minor HP recovery (optional)

**Enemy Encounter Risk:**

- DM rolls (e.g., D6, on 1-2 = encounter)
- Players must choose: Continue resting OR defend

### **Long Rest**

**Requirements:**

- 1 ration per person
- Safe location (or risk ambush)
- Full day/night of downtime

**Benefits:**

- Restore all magic charges
- Heal HP (amount determined by DM/setting)
- Remove temporary starvation penalties (if fed)
- Reset daily resources (Luck rerolls if using pool system)
- Armor/weapon maintenance

### **Crafting During Rest**

**Process:**

1. Have recipe/blueprint + required materials
2. Roll crafting skill check
3. Complex items may require **multiple short rests**

**Outcomes:**

|Result|Effect|
|---|---|
|**Critical Success (Nat 1)**|Superior version! Bonus stats OR leftover materials|
|**Success**|Item crafted as intended|
|**Failure**|Weaker version (reduced stats) OR materials damaged (50% loss)|
|**Critical Failure (Nat 20)**|Materials destroyed, item unusable|

**Time Investment:**

- Simple repair: 1 short rest, easy check
- Custom weapon mod: 2 short rests, moderate check
- Experimental tech: 3+ short rests, hard check

