## **11. ECONOMY & LOOTING**

### **Money Acquisition**

**Money is NOT awarded per encounter automatically.**

Instead, players must **loot bodies/containers** after combat:

- Takes time (can't loot mid-combat)
- Roll on Loot Table per body/container
- Luck stat may modify loot rolls

### **Loot Table**

Roll D20:

|Roll|Result|
|---|---|
|1-5|Nothing / junk|
|6-8|1-2 rations|
|9-10|Small credits (10-50)|
|11-14|Consumables (ammo, medkits)|
|15-17|Weapon/armor (common tier)|
|18-19|Augments/special items|
|20|Rare gear or large credits|

**Luck Modifiers (Optional):**

- High Luck = +1 or +2 to loot rolls
- OR: Luck allows one reroll per encounter on loot table

### **Selling Equipment**

**Option A: Equal Exchange**

- Sell items for same price you paid
- Player-friendly, no punishment for experimentation

**Option B: Condition-Based**

- Damaged/used gear sells for less
- Pristine gear sells at full value
- Adds economic pressure

### **Augments & Installation**

**Finding Augments:**

- Can be looted (rare)
- Purchased from specialty vendors

**Installation Required:**

- Cannot equip augments directly
- Must visit specialist (Ripper Doc, Artificer, Tech Surgeon, etc.)
- **Installation costs money** (creates economic sink)
- May require downtime recovery

