## **13. ENVIRONMENTAL HAZARDS**

### **Weather & Environmental Conditions**

|Hazard|Effect|
|---|---|
|**Sandstorm**|-2 to accuracy rolls, 1 damage/turn (or CON check to resist)|
|**Rain**|Movement checks required (DEX check or slip), -1 accuracy|
|**Fog**|Reduced visibility (halve weapon range)|
|**Extreme Heat**|CON checks per turn or take fatigue damage|
|**Extreme Cold**|Speed reduced, fingers numb (reload costs +1 action slot)|

### **Severe Hazards**

- **Earthquake:** Everyone rolls DEX or fall prone, structures may collapse
- **Tornado:** Must flee or find shelter immediately (no combat possible)
- **Wildfire:** Spreading damage zones, creates dynamic terrain changes

### **Hazard Application**

**Recommended: Narrative-Driven**

- DM describes scene and applies appropriate hazard effects
- Use hazards to create tension and tactical variety

**Optional: Random Hazard Table**

Roll D12 when entering new area:

|Roll|Hazard Level|
|---|---|
|1-6|Clear conditions|
|7-8|Minor hazard (rain, wind)|
|9-10|Moderate hazard (sandstorm, fog)|
|11-12|Severe hazard (tornado, earthquake)|

